    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim Version\n\nNVIM v0.5.0-dev+1115-gc1fbc2ddf\n\n### Operating system/version:\n\nWSL Ubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version:\n\nmintty 3.4.5\n\n### TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nvimrc:\r\n```vim\r\nset autochdir\r\n\r\nautocmd CmdlineLeave * call Leave()\r\n\r\nlet s:buf = nvim_create_buf(0, 1)\r\ncall nvim_buf_set_name(s:buf, 'Foo')\r\n\r\nfunction! Leave()\r\n  let l:win = nvim_open_win(s:buf, 0, {\r\n        \\ 'relative': 'editor',\r\n        \\ 'height': 1,\r\n        \\ 'width': 1,\r\n        \\ 'row': 0,\r\n        \\ 'col': 0,\r\n        \\ })\r\n  call nvim_win_close(l:win, 1)\r\nendfunction\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. Open nvim: `nvim -u vimrc`.\r\n2. Edit a file in a different directory: `:e ~/foo/bar.txt`\r\n3. Check pwd: `pwd`\n\n### Vim\n\nNo, Vim doesn't have floating windows\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`pwd` should show `~/foo`.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`pwd` shows `~`.",
    "closed_at": "2024-04-16T11:49:57Z",
